FBIS3-53509 "drnes011_p_94009" FBIS-NES-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Official Notes Government's Position on Peace LD1701205694 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 0230 GMT 17 Jan 94 LD1701205694 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Language: Pashto Article Type:BFN [Text] Afghanistan welcomes all efforts to bring about a permanent peace. Dr. Najibollah Lefrai, state minister in foreign affairs, told a Bakhtar Information Agency that an Afghan special envoy, who has recently gone to Pakistan, has delivered a message from the Afghan president to Pakistan's president at a meeting. They talked about a permanent peace and explained our principled stand. Dr. Lefrai said the position taken by Afghanistan has not changed. The conspirators should surrender their heavy weapons. The Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of Afghanistan] lead by Golboddin Hekmatyar should give guarantees of no more war against the state.
